<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

							Balanced Inventory of Desirable Responding (BIDR)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 05-06-2016
last updated:  02-17-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-17-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
This script implements the Balanced Inventory of Desirable Responding as described in:

Paulhus, D. L. (1984). Two-component models of socially desirable responding. 
Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 46, 598-609.

The BIDR is intended to measure self-deceptive positivity and impression management.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
40 7-point Likert questions
1-20: assess self-deceptive positivity
21-40: assess impression management
											  
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 4 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'bidr.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	 with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					scores given for response selected (in assigned values: 0-1) - reversed items are automatically reversed scored
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)


(2) Summary data file: 'bidr_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

BIDR_total:						total score for the BIDR (0-40)
								=> the higher the score the more questions were answered with a 
								socially desired response

SDP:							score for the self-deceptive positivity scale (0-20)
IM:								score for the impression management scale (0-20)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
QUESTIONNAIRE SET-UP & SCORING
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

The original responses are scored on a scale of 1-7:

all responses < 6: score as 0
all responses >= 6: score as 1 

R = reversed scoring applied

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
see section Editable Parameters

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:		the general instructions that appear on the surveypages

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Please rate how much you agree with the following statements.

"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.00%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed, 
expressions.BIDR_total, expressions.SDP, expressions.IM)
</summarydata>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/SDP:		score for the self-deceptive positivity scale
/IM:		score for the impression management scale
BIDR_total:	total score for the BIDR

<expressions>
/SDP = radiobuttons.q1.response + radiobuttons.q2_R.response + radiobuttons.q3.response + radiobuttons.q4_R.response +
radiobuttons.q5.response + radiobuttons.q6_R.response + radiobuttons.q7.response + radiobuttons.q8_R.response +
radiobuttons.q9.response + radiobuttons.q10_R.response + radiobuttons.q11.response + radiobuttons.q12_R.response +
radiobuttons.q13.response + radiobuttons.q14_R.response + radiobuttons.q15.response + radiobuttons.q16_R.response +
radiobuttons.q17.response + radiobuttons.q18_R.response + radiobuttons.q19.response + radiobuttons.q20_R.response
/IM = radiobuttons.q21_R.response + radiobuttons.q22.response + radiobuttons.q23_R.response + radiobuttons.q24.response +
radiobuttons.q25_R.response + radiobuttons.q26.response + radiobuttons.q27_R.response + radiobuttons.q28.response +
radiobuttons.q29_R.response + radiobuttons.q30.response + radiobuttons.q31_R.response + radiobuttons.q32.response +
radiobuttons.q33_R.response + radiobuttons.q34.response + radiobuttons.q35_R.response + radiobuttons.q36.response +
radiobuttons.q37_R.response + radiobuttons.q38.response + radiobuttons.q39_R.response + radiobuttons.q40.response
/BIDR_total = expressions.SDP + expressions.IM
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "1. My first impressions of people usually turns out to be right."
/ options = ("1~nNot true", "2", "3", "4~nSomewhat~ntrue", "5", "6", "7~nVery true")
/ optionvalues = ("0","0", "0", "0", "0", "1", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2_R>
/caption = "2. It would be hard for me to break any of my bad habits."
/ options = ("1~nNot true", "2", "3", "4~nSomewhat~ntrue", "5", "6", "7~nVery true")
/ optionvalues = ("1","1", "0", "0", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3>
/caption = "3. I don’t care to know what other people really think of me."
/ options = ("1~nNot true", "2", "3", "4~nSomewhat~ntrue", "5", "6", "7~nVery true")
/ optionvalues = ("0","0", "0", "0", "0", "1", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4_R>
/caption = "4. I have not always been honest with myself."
/ options = ("1~nNot true", "2", "3", "4~nSomewhat~ntrue", "5", "6", "7~nVery true")
/ optionvalues = ("1","1", "0", "0", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5>
/caption = "5. I always know why I like things."
/ options = ("1~nNot true", "2", "3", "4~nSomewhat~ntrue", "5", "6", "7~nVery true")
/ optionvalues = ("0","0", "0", "0", "0", "1", "1")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6_R>
/caption = "6. When my emotions are aroused, it biases my thinking."
/ options = ("1~nNot true", "2", "3", "4~nSomewhat~ntrue", "5", "6", "7~nVery true")
/ optionvalues = ("1","1", "0", "0", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7>
/caption = "7. Once I’ve made up my mind, other people can seldom change my opinion."
/ options = ("1~nNot true", "2", "3", "4~nSomewhat~ntrue", "5", "6", "7~nVery true")
/ optionvalues = ("0","0", "0", "0", "0", "1", "1")
